The paper deals with a delay-sensitive information flow problem over a directed graph, which is a typical problem in network information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The problem involves finding an optimal path or paths to minimize the maximum end-to-end delay, which is a typical optimization problem in computer science. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity) are also likely sub-categories. The paper proposes an algorithm to solve the problem, which involves computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information theory and coding theory, which are typical topics in cs.IT (Information Theory).
